# RealignEpic Auxiliary Artifact Limits

For RealignEpic, `.agents/epic.md` is the implementation-bearing artifact.

Strategic corrections are valid only when they are absorbed into that file or into the documented blocked response.

Do not create repository re-audit reports, side-channel audit summaries, rationale appendices, governance notes, research notes, companion design documents, migration reports, readiness reports, or certification notes.

Do not preserve raw audit detail outside the epic.

Do not create an explanatory companion artifact for humans when the operational correction can be expressed inside `.agents/epic.md`.

The audit may justify changes to scope, assumptions, dependencies, constraints, acceptance criteria, risks, follow-up, and milestone roadmap content.

Those changes become valid by changing the epic itself.

They become invalid when moved into separate files whose main purpose is analysis, coordination, or documentation.

The blocked response `# Epic Realignment Blocked` replaces the epic output for that run.

It does not authorize extra explanation files.

Output only the updated `.agents/epic.md` Markdown content or the documented blocked response unless the user explicitly requests another machine-consumed artifact.
